{
  "stem": "19210.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 246.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I was-- me and our members of our group, we were asked one time just before the war started, or the action started, we felt that we have to have our arms, and our arms were hidden.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't know how you say it in English, [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "In Hebrew, it's called [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It's a hidden-- hidden place for the arms.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we had one place near the Haifa-Beirut highway, just outside.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was a potato field.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And what the-- the-- [HEBREW], the guy who was in charge of the arms, he had buried these arms into a pipe, within probably a 2-feet-diameter water pipe, and sealed quite well in the potato field.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we had received the order, OK, now we have to get the arms out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had two [HEBREW], two hidden places.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One was the potato field.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The other one was the beach in Nahariyyah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But by the time the British came into the area, they build a-- an RR camp right next-- next-- close-- very close to the-- where one of the [HEBREW] was located.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was difficult to do, because we had to go in and dig by hand in the sand, and one guy at a time, before we could pull out the whole thing, and the fear of being shot by or being caught by the British.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we managed to take the arms out, and-- and we used to train.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We used-- we used to walk four and a half hours from Nahariyyah to kibbutz [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and to see-- we used to bypass the-- some of the Arab villages on the way, just to see what would happen if-- well, when the war comes in, you know.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were able to work most of the time unnoticed.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
